## Level 4 Checkpoint

Below is the complete code for a simple task manager app. It has a heading, a list of tasks, a button to toggle tasks as "done," and some styling. But there are **four intentional bugs** — one in HTML, one in CSS, and two in JavaScript.

Read through all three files carefully. Then answer the questions to find each bug.

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Task Manager</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>My Tasks</h1>
    <ul id="task-list">
      <li class="task" data-id="1">
        <span class="task-text">Buy groceries</span>
        <button class="done-btn">Done</button>
      </li>
      <li class="task" data-id="2">
        <span class="task-text">Reply to emails</span>
        <button class="done-btn">Done</button>
      </li>
      <li class="task" data-id="3">
        <span class="task-text">Schedule team meeting<span>
        <button class="done-btn">Done</button>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="summary">Click "Done" to mark tasks as completed.</p>
  </div>
  <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

```css
/* styles.css */
.container {
  max-width: 500px;
  margin: 40px auto;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

.task {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

.task-text {
  font-size: 16px;
}

.task.completed .task-text {
  text-decoration: line-through;
  color: #999;
}

.done-btn {
  background: #4CAF50;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.done-btn:hover {
  background: #45a049;
}

.summary {
  color: #666;
  margin-top: 20px;
